# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: MagePath | Scene: MagePath2
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "For little over a week, Sarah had stayed in Xan's house."
    new "For little over a week, Sarah had stayed in Xan's house."

    old "Every day she sat out on her task to keep it clean, picking up the dishes, clearing out his discarded books, folding his laundry."
    new "Every day she sat out on her task to keep it clean, picking up the dishes, clearing out his discarded books, folding his laundry."

    old "And every day she also set out some time to delve deeper into the house, cleaning up one of the rarely used rooms."
    new "And every day she also set out some time to delve deeper into the house, cleaning up one of the rarely used rooms."

    old "It was an odd thing, the way in which the dimensions from the house betrayed its outward appearance."
    new "It was an odd thing, the way in which the dimensions from the house betrayed its outward appearance."

    old "Room after room revealed itself to her."
    new "Room after room revealed itself to her."

    old "Sarah would have sworn that from the inside, the house was bigger than the inside."
    new "Sarah would have sworn that from the inside, the house was bigger than the inside."

    old "She shook her head. Absurd."
    new "She shook her head. Absurd."

    old "She and Xan had set into an easy routine."
    new "She and Xan had set into an easy routine."

    old "He was at every moment absorbed into one of his many books, and only late at night did Sarah occasionally manage to lure him away from the books for a conversation."
    new "He was at every moment absorbed into one of his many books, and only late at night did Sarah occasionally manage to lure him away from the books for a conversation."

    old "He was a researcher, he hadn't said much more about it, and Sarah had not pressed him."
    new "He was a researcher, he hadn't said much more about it, and Sarah had not pressed him."

    old "She was his guest, and she thought it rude to ask too many questions."
    new "She was his guest, and she thought it rude to ask too many questions."

    old "Also, though she did not say it to herself, she feared what might happen if he kicked her out."
    new "Also, though she did not say it to herself, she feared what might happen if he kicked her out."

    old "Sarah clung on to the little bit of certainty that she now had in her life."
    new "Sarah clung on to the little bit of certainty that she now had in her life."

    old "Today, she had reached the door at the end of the hallway. Opening it, she found a room with no windows."
    new "Today, she had reached the door at the end of the hallway. Opening it, she found a room with no windows."

    old "The only thing that seemed different was that this one appeared to be more in use than the others."
    new "The only thing that seemed different was that this one appeared to be more in use than the others."

    old "Still, this too was not too strange. Xan often wandered around the house. She would often find him sitting in odd corners, reading his books."
    new "Still, this too was not too strange. Xan often wandered around the house. She would often find him sitting in odd corners, reading his books."

    old "Sarah pulled the rag over her face and set on her task of dusting any and every surface she could find."
    new "Sarah pulled the rag over her face and set on her task of dusting any and every surface she could find."

    old "It was an endless task, and yet, Sarah was glad for the distraction."
    new "It was an endless task, and yet, Sarah was glad for the distraction."

    old "She had started in the corner, working her way towards the end of the room, when she slid her duster across a series of glass containers at the back."
    new "She had started in the corner, working her way towards the end of the room, when she slid her duster across a series of glass containers at the back."

    old "A shudder moved through her, and what little light was in the room, seemed to dim."
    new "A shudder moved through her, and what little light was in the room, seemed to dim."

    old "Sarah instinctively leapt back as a thick smoke emerged from one of the containers."
    new "Sarah instinctively leapt back as a thick smoke emerged from one of the containers."

    old "Thick and black like ink, she thought for a moment that she had knocked something over, even though she was sure she had not."
    new "Thick and black like ink, she thought for a moment that she had knocked something over, even though she was sure she had not."

    old "Then, her horror grew as the smoke moved so very much unlike smoke. Weaving and bending back down, as though possessing a mind."
    new "Then, her horror grew as the smoke moved so very much unlike smoke. Weaving and bending back down, as though possessing a mind."

    old "Emerging from the inky blackness, something that approximated a face of some kind."
    new "Emerging from the inky blackness, something that approximated a face of some kind."

    old "What now, mage?"
    new "What now, mage?"

    old "Can't you let me be?"
    new "Can't you let me be?"

    old "Sarah felt pinned to the floor as the creature spoke. It's voice was smooth like its ethereal body."
    new "Sarah felt pinned to the floor as the creature spoke. It's voice was smooth like its ethereal body."

    old "The thing's eyes shifted through its body, until they suddenly found and fixed on Sarah."
    new "The thing's eyes shifted through its body, until they suddenly found and fixed on Sarah."

    old "You're not that decrepit wizard..."
    new "You're not that decrepit wizard..."

    old "The smoke that made up the body of the thing, or what passed for a body, swirled around."
    new "The smoke that made up the body of the thing, or what passed for a body, swirled around."

    old "At the base, Sarah could see it emerged from a glass flask. It seemed attached to it in some way."
    new "At the base, Sarah could see it emerged from a glass flask. It seemed attached to it in some way."

    old "In all her life, she had never heard of such a creature, not even in books or stories."
    new "In all her life, she had never heard of such a creature, not even in books or stories."

    old "I...I'm...Sarah..."
    new "I...I'm...Sarah..."

    old "The thing paused."
    new "The thing paused."

    old "It's been a long time since he's let anyone into his house."
    new "It's been a long time since he's let anyone into his house."

    old "Sarah didn't know how to respond to this...creature. Was it dangerous? It seemed above all, unnatural."
    new "Sarah didn't know how to respond to this...creature. Was it dangerous? It seemed above all, unnatural."

    old "Not unnatural in the way that things were odd, but unnatural as if this thing was truly seperate from the natural order, belonging to a different world."
    new "Not unnatural in the way that things were odd, but unnatural as if this thing was truly seperate from the natural order, belonging to a different world."

    old "The smoke swirled, twirling around in whimsical delight."
    new "The smoke swirled, twirling around in whimsical delight."

    old "You can't be blind to how men look at you."
    new "You can't be blind to how men look at you."

    old "I imagine you've had to suffer their eyes all your life."
    new "I imagine you've had to suffer their eyes all your life."

    old "Always being seen for your body, so rarely for who you are..."
    new "Always being seen for your body, so rarely for who you are..."

    old "Tell me, Sarah, are you anything at all?"
    new "Tell me, Sarah, are you anything at all?"

    old "Sarah swallowed, but her mouth was still dry."
    new "Sarah swallowed, but her mouth was still dry."

    old "Sarah racked her brain, trying to find an answer to that question that didn't sound absurd."
    new "Sarah racked her brain, trying to find an answer to that question that didn't sound absurd."

    old "I'm a princess..."
    new "I'm a princess..."

    old "You were one..."
    new "You were one..."

    old "How could this creature know."
    new "How could this creature know."

    old "Also, that's merely a title, easily won or lost. Tell me truly...what are you?"
    new "Also, that's merely a title, easily won or lost. Tell me truly...what are you?"

    old "Sarah begun to have enough of the creature."
    new "Sarah begun to have enough of the creature."

    old "I don't have to answer you."
    new "I don't have to answer you."

    old "The smoke moved again, but it seemed contained to its corner of the room, unwilling or unable to move much further."
    new "The smoke moved again, but it seemed contained to its corner of the room, unwilling or unable to move much further."

    old "This is true. You owe me no answer. I'm just a simple spirit, bored and happy to meet a new friend."
    new "This is true. You owe me no answer. I'm just a simple spirit, bored and happy to meet a new friend."

    old "I know what I am..."
    new "I know what I am..."

    old "It paused."
    new "It paused."

    old "Do you know what Xanthippe is?"
    new "Do you know what Xanthippe is?"

    old "Sarah slowly brought herself to her feet, afraid that if she rose too fast, the thing might attack."
    new "Sarah slowly brought herself to her feet, afraid that if she rose too fast, the thing might attack."

    old "Though, it had called her a friend. Could it be such a thing?"
    new "Though, it had called her a friend. Could it be such a thing?"

    old "Sneaky..."
    new "Sneaky..."

    old "He comes near!"
    new "He comes near!"

    old "He's heard us!"
    new "He's heard us!"

    old "Come to me tonight and I will tell you!"
    new "Come to me tonight and I will tell you!"

    old "The door bursts open."
    new "The door bursts open."

    old "Xan rushed in, placing himself between Sarah and the creature."
    new "Xan rushed in, placing himself between Sarah and the creature."

    old "A light radiated from each of his hands, swirling around his arms, driving back the darkness."
    new "A light radiated from each of his hands, swirling around his arms, driving back the darkness."

    old "The creature seemed to cower under its mere radiance."
    new "The creature seemed to cower under its mere radiance."

    old "Go back, Razaphel, go back into your flask or I swear I'll give you a thrasing that you will remember for a thousand years."
    new "Go back, Razaphel, go back into your flask or I swear I'll give you a thrasing that you will remember for a thousand years."

    old "The smoke began to pull back, receding back into the flask from which it first emerged."
    new "The smoke began to pull back, receding back into the flask from which it first emerged."

    old "Forgive me, master. I have only sought to make the acquaintance of our new visitor."
    new "Forgive me, master. I have only sought to make the acquaintance of our new visitor."

    old "Back into your flask, now!"
    new "Back into your flask, now!"

    old "The creature's teeth and eyes faded back into its inky body, as the last of it dissapeared back into the flask."
    new "The creature's teeth and eyes faded back into its inky body, as the last of it dissapeared back into the flask."

    old "Inside of it, Sarah could see it swirl."
    new "Inside of it, Sarah could see it swirl."

    old "Finally, Xan turned around to Sarah."
    new "Finally, Xan turned around to Sarah."

    old "Are you fine? Did he say anything?"
    new "Are you fine? Did he say anything?"

    old "I'm fine...it just...wanted to talk."
    new "I'm fine...it just...wanted to talk."

    old "Xan sighed, relieved."
    new "Xan sighed, relieved."

    old "Yeah, he likes to do that, talk. He'll talk all day if you let him."
    new "Yeah, he likes to do that, talk. He'll talk all day if you let him."

    old "What...what is it? I've never seen anything like it before."
    new "What...what is it? I've never seen anything like it before."

    old "Xan tossled his own hair, trying to find the words to explain."
    new "Xan tossled his own hair, trying to find the words to explain."

    old "You're right that you've never seen such a thing. They're rare, in our world anyway, I can't imagine there are more than a dozen in the entire world."
    new "You're right that you've never seen such a thing. They're rare, in our world anyway, I can't imagine there are more than a dozen in the entire world."

    old "But...what is it, exactly?"
    new "But...what is it, exactly?"

    old "They're called a lot of things, but my order, we call them voidlings."
    new "They're called a lot of things, but my order, we call them voidlings."

    old "They are creatures of the void, born out of the shadows in the under realm."
    new "They are creatures of the void, born out of the shadows in the under realm."

    old "Sarah stared at Xan, confused. She'd never heard of any of this before."
    new "Sarah stared at Xan, confused. She'd never heard of any of this before."

    old "Xan sighed."
    new "Xan sighed."

    old "I'll tell you the story as briefly as I can."
    new "I'll tell you the story as briefly as I can."

    old "Many millenia ago, this world didn't have the many different kingdoms it has today."
    new "Many millenia ago, this world didn't have the many different kingdoms it has today."

    old "There was only one great empire, and it ruled all the world. There wasn't much of a world to rule, but in a savage time, they were the only real civilization."
    new "There was only one great empire, and it ruled all the world. There wasn't much of a world to rule, but in a savage time, they were the only real civilization."

    old "They worshipped a pantheon of gods, and the rulers of this civilization could speak to them directly, as easily as you or I can speak to each other."
    new "They worshipped a pantheon of gods, and the rulers of this civilization could speak to them directly, as easily as you or I can speak to each other."

    old "For centuries, this allowed them to guide humanity to its earliest forms of progress."
    new "For centuries, this allowed them to guide humanity to its earliest forms of progress."

    old "All of this continued until the rule of empress Ayamari."
    new "All of this continued until the rule of empress Ayamari."

    old "Empress Ayamari was more gifted than any who had come before her. Brilliant in ways the world had not yet seen before."
    new "Empress Ayamari was more gifted than any who had come before her. Brilliant in ways the world had not yet seen before."

    old "As gifted as she was in knowledge and wisdom, so gifted was she too in her beauty."
    new "As gifted as she was in knowledge and wisdom, so gifted was she too in her beauty."

    old "Everyone longed to serve her, if only to to be in the presence of her grace."
    new "Everyone longed to serve her, if only to to be in the presence of her grace."

    old "Xan paused for a moment, collecting himself."
    new "Xan paused for a moment, collecting himself."

    old "She ruled for a long time, and the empire reached its peak. But then, as is the fate of all humans, age came for her."
    new "She ruled for a long time, and the empire reached its peak. But then, as is the fate of all humans, age came for her."

    old "She grew older and more sickly, and all the empire wept, but above all, empress Ayamari herself wept."
    new "She grew older and more sickly, and all the empire wept, but above all, empress Ayamari herself wept."

    old "She cried for the empire that she would leave behind, and she feared what would become of her people once she was gone."
    new "She cried for the empire that she would leave behind, and she feared what would become of her people once she was gone."

    old "This fear and this love for her people and her empire, caused her to reach out to the gods."
    new "This fear and this love for her people and her empire, caused her to reach out to the gods."

    old "As they had always done, they reached back down and spoke to her."
    new "As they had always done, they reached back down and spoke to her."

    old "She called out and said that she was the fairest and wisest ruler the empire had ever seen."
    new "She called out and said that she was the fairest and wisest ruler the empire had ever seen."

    old "To this, the gods agreed."
    new "To this, the gods agreed."

    old "And so, she said, the gods should allow her to live forever. Let her live as long as the gods themselves and rule her empire with wisdom and kindness for all time."
    new "And so, she said, the gods should allow her to live forever. Let her live as long as the gods themselves and rule her empire with wisdom and kindness for all time."

    old "But to this, the gods did not agree."
    new "But to this, the gods did not agree."

    old "Only the gods live forever, and so, they scolded her for her ambitions, and did not grant her desire."
    new "Only the gods live forever, and so, they scolded her for her ambitions, and did not grant her desire."

    old "Empress Ayamari fell into a great despair, feeling that death would soon come for her, leaving the empire without her guidance."
    new "Empress Ayamari fell into a great despair, feeling that death would soon come for her, leaving the empire without her guidance."

    old "Not the gods, nor any science they had, could offer her eternal life. She wept most every day."
    new "Not the gods, nor any science they had, could offer her eternal life. She wept most every day."

    old "That was, until a thought came to her."
    new "That was, until a thought came to her."

    old "A thought that perhaps, if these gods would not grant her request, she ought to ask the gods of another world."
    new "A thought that perhaps, if these gods would not grant her request, she ought to ask the gods of another world."

    old "Empress Ayamari believed there must be many worlds out there, who each had their own gods. In such a great universe, surely, one would answer her desire and let her save her people?"
    new "Empress Ayamari believed there must be many worlds out there, who each had their own gods. In such a great universe, surely, one would answer her desire and let her save her people?"

    old "A tear ran past Xan's face."
    new "A tear ran past Xan's face."

    old "The research began and soon a suitable ritual was found."
    new "The research began and soon a suitable ritual was found."

    old "After months of preparation, the ritual was carried out and another world was summoned into ours."
    new "After months of preparation, the ritual was carried out and another world was summoned into ours."

    old "This new world was summoned into ours, but all of existence covers all of existence."
    new "This new world was summoned into ours, but all of existence covers all of existence."

    old "And so, our plane of existence collapsed onto this new world which had been summoned, trapping their existence underneath ours."
    new "And so, our plane of existence collapsed onto this new world which had been summoned, trapping their existence underneath ours."

    old "So violent was this merger, that all across our world, rips and tears spawned, and from them, hordes of these voidlings spawned forth."
    new "So violent was this merger, that all across our world, rips and tears spawned, and from them, hordes of these voidlings spawned forth."

    old "The empire fell into chaos as it sacrificed everything to fight back against the tide."
    new "The empire fell into chaos as it sacrificed everything to fight back against the tide."

    old "The pantheon of gods became silent, and no longer answered the calls of humanity."
    new "The pantheon of gods became silent, and no longer answered the calls of humanity."

    old "By the end, the voidlings had been either destroyed or thrown back into their world, and the last of the scars of reality were closed."
    new "By the end, the voidlings had been either destroyed or thrown back into their world, and the last of the scars of reality were closed."

    old "But the empire was ruined. All across, warlords and other men of ambition seized on their chance, and it splintered."
    new "But the empire was ruined. All across, warlords and other men of ambition seized on their chance, and it splintered."

    old "The portals between the world were seperated, but the fundamental relation has remained the same ever since."
    new "The portals between the world were seperated, but the fundamental relation has remained the same ever since."

    old "Our world sits balanced atop their world, which runs underneath ours."
    new "Our world sits balanced atop their world, which runs underneath ours."

    old "Sarah listened intently, trying to take all of this in."
    new "Sarah listened intently, trying to take all of this in."

    old "How could an entire history like this exist an be unknown to her?"
    new "How could an entire history like this exist an be unknown to her?"

    old "But, if our worlds are seperate, how can this creature exist here?"
    new "But, if our worlds are seperate, how can this creature exist here?"

    old "Xan looked away."
    new "Xan looked away."

    old "That's perhaps a story best left for another time."
    new "That's perhaps a story best left for another time."

    old "He told her this much, but Sarah realized, there was much more he kept from her."
    new "He told her this much, but Sarah realized, there was much more he kept from her."

    old "Don't press, she reminded herself."
    new "Don't press, she reminded herself."

    old "That's fine, Xan. Thank you for telling me all this. I've never heard of it before."
    new "That's fine, Xan. Thank you for telling me all this. I've never heard of it before."

    old "Yes, it's so long ago, and so many empires rose and fell, the story has been lost to most people, except for my order."
    new "Yes, it's so long ago, and so many empires rose and fell, the story has been lost to most people, except for my order."

    old "Come, let's retreat back to the living room, it's almost time for dinner."
    new "Come, let's retreat back to the living room, it's almost time for dinner."

    old "Together, they left the room and the spirit to itself."
    new "Together, they left the room and the spirit to itself."

    old "In the warmth of the living room, they ate and spoke, but not long after, Xan fell back distracted into his books."
    new "In the warmth of the living room, they ate and spoke, but not long after, Xan fell back distracted into his books."

    old "Sarah told him she was going to sleep, but if he heard her, Xan gave no indication."
    new "Sarah told him she was going to sleep, but if he heard her, Xan gave no indication."

    old "Sarah collapsed into her bed, staring at the ceiling."
    new "Sarah collapsed into her bed, staring at the ceiling."

    old "Moments turned to hours as she spend trying to make sense of everything that Xan had told her."
    new "Moments turned to hours as she spend trying to make sense of everything that Xan had told her."

    old "Outside, the city softly fell asleep, while Sarah could not."
    new "Outside, the city softly fell asleep, while Sarah could not."

    old "Creatures like this, secret histories..."
    new "Creatures like this, secret histories..."

    old "She had enjoyed the simplicity that came with housekeeping, but now she once again found her world filling with complexities."
    new "She had enjoyed the simplicity that came with housekeeping, but now she once again found her world filling with complexities."

    old "Sneak out and visit the spirit."
    new "Sneak out and visit the spirit."

    old "Sarah remembered the spirit's final words. He had invited her to come back to him that night, to give her more answers."
    new "Sarah remembered the spirit's final words. He had invited her to come back to him that night, to give her more answers."

    old "It was answers that she craved."
    new "It was answers that she craved."

    old "Sarah slowly got dressed and snuck out into the hallway."
    new "Sarah slowly got dressed and snuck out into the hallway."

    old "All around her, the house was dark and quiet."
    new "All around her, the house was dark and quiet."

    old "She considered every step, fearful that she would step on a loose plank and wake Xan. If he was even asleep at all."
    new "She considered every step, fearful that she would step on a loose plank and wake Xan. If he was even asleep at all."

    old "In a mere few steps, she found herself at the end of the hallway."
    new "In a mere few steps, she found herself at the end of the hallway."

    old "She slipped back into the room where she had first met the spirit that day."
    new "She slipped back into the room where she had first met the spirit that day."

    old "Poorly lit, she could make out just enough to find her way back to the shelf filled with flasks."
    new "Poorly lit, she could make out just enough to find her way back to the shelf filled with flasks."

    old "She steeled her heart and called out."
    new "She steeled her heart and called out."

    old "Spirit..."
    new "Spirit..."

    old "Nothing stirred."
    new "Nothing stirred."

    old "Spirit...it's me...Sarah..."
    new "Spirit...it's me...Sarah..."

    old "At first, nothing."
    new "At first, nothing."

    old "But then, slowly, as it had before, the mist began to swirl and dance forth from the flask."
    new "But then, slowly, as it had before, the mist began to swirl and dance forth from the flask."

    old "Soon after it took form, its hollow eyes and blank face emerged."
    new "Soon after it took form, its hollow eyes and blank face emerged."

    old "In the same moment as the spirit stirred, blue runes etched into the floor began to hum and radiate with blue light."
    new "In the same moment as the spirit stirred, blue runes etched into the floor began to hum and radiate with blue light."

    old "My new friend has come to visit."
    new "My new friend has come to visit."

    old "Tell me, where does the mage hide? Just outside the door, so he can punish me again?"
    new "Tell me, where does the mage hide? Just outside the door, so he can punish me again?"

    old "Xan doesn't know I'm here. I sneaked out."
    new "Xan doesn't know I'm here. I sneaked out."

    old "The thing's face shifted."
    new "The thing's face shifted."

    old "And here I thought you were but another servant girl. But this one has a mind of her own."
    new "And here I thought you were but another servant girl. But this one has a mind of her own."

    old "I came because you asked."
    new "I came because you asked."

    old "I did...and yet, I thought you would not come."
    new "I did...and yet, I thought you would not come."

    old "Because I frighten you."
    new "Because I frighten you."

    old "Sarah swallowed. Honesty would serve her best, she imagined."
    new "Sarah swallowed. Honesty would serve her best, she imagined."

    old "You do."
    new "You do."

    old "Most who see me, fear me. Best I suppose that so few see me at all."
    new "Most who see me, fear me. Best I suppose that so few see me at all."

    old "Are you lonely?"
    new "Are you lonely?"

    old "Something like a laughter flowed forth from the spirit."
    new "Something like a laughter flowed forth from the spirit."

    old "I've been on this plane a long time, but you're the first to ask me that."
    new "I've been on this plane a long time, but you're the first to ask me that."

    old "Is that what brought you here? To discuss this old spirit's feelings?"
    new "Is that what brought you here? To discuss this old spirit's feelings?"

    old "You told me...that you know who Xan is...that he keeps secrets from me..."
    new "You told me...that you know who Xan is...that he keeps secrets from me..."

    old "This I did."
    new "This I did."

    old "Then tell me. Tell me what I need to know. Answer the questions that I don't even know how to ask."
    new "Then tell me. Tell me what I need to know. Answer the questions that I don't even know how to ask."

    old "The smoke shifted from one end to the other, turning around upon itself."
    new "The smoke shifted from one end to the other, turning around upon itself."

    old "You will have your answers, but I offer up nothing for free. All things have a price."
    new "You will have your answers, but I offer up nothing for free. All things have a price."

    old "A price?"
    new "A price?"

    old "Yes, Sarah, my new friend."
    new "Yes, Sarah, my new friend."

    old "Take off your clothes and cross the threshold into the circle."
    new "Take off your clothes and cross the threshold into the circle."

    old "Sarah was stunned at the spirit's request."
    new "Sarah was stunned at the spirit's request."

    old "My clothes?"
    new "My clothes?"

    old "Yes, if you want your answers, you will have to give up your body to me."
    new "Yes, if you want your answers, you will have to give up your body to me."

    old "Sarah felt herself turn red, even here in the dark."
    new "Sarah felt herself turn red, even here in the dark."

    old "For some reason, she had imagined the spirit to be above such base desires."
    new "For some reason, she had imagined the spirit to be above such base desires."

    old "Take off your clothes."
    new "Take off your clothes."

    old "If this is what it takes, Sarah thought, she would offer it up for knowledge."
    new "If this is what it takes, Sarah thought, she would offer it up for knowledge."

    old "She slid her hands across the straps on her dress, sliding them off her shoulder, letting her dress fall to the ground."
    new "She slid her hands across the straps on her dress, sliding them off her shoulder, letting her dress fall to the ground."

    old "She could see the spirit stir already."
    new "She could see the spirit stir already."

    old "Unclasping her bra and sliding off her underwear, Sarah soon found herself standing naked in the room."
    new "Unclasping her bra and sliding off her underwear, Sarah soon found herself standing naked in the room."

    old "Enter the circle..."
